##CHANGELOG
All notable changes to this project are documented in this file.

#April 1, 2024 — Initial Program Structure
Added
Basic program framework for drivetrain calculations.

Excel data loading using readtable with automatic column‑name preservation.

Automatic detection of key columns (motor RPM, input gear, output gear, wheel speed).

Initial filtering system based on selected motor RPM.

#April 5, 2024 — Wheel Size Detection
Added
Regex‑based extraction of wheel diameters from column headers.

Dynamic wheel‑size menu populated only with valid wheel options.

Filtering now respects both motor RPM and wheel diameter.

#April 10, 2024 — Gear Selection System
Added
Detection of direct‑drive (1:1) availability.

Input gear menu now shows only valid gears for the selected wheel and RPM.

Output gear menu now shows only valid gears for the selected input gear.

Prevented invalid gear combinations from appearing in menus.

#April 15, 2024 — Speed and Torque Calculations
Added
Gear ratio calculation for both direct and geared drive.

Wheel speed extraction from the selected wheel column.

Torque‑at‑wheel calculation using stall torque multiplied by gear ratio.

Summary output showing all selected drivetrain parameters.

#April 22, 2024 — Physical Fit Warning System
Added
Warning when the output gear is larger than the selected wheel.

Warning when required gear spacing does not match standard VEX 0.5‑inch hole spacing.

Red text warnings using fprintf(2, ...).

System allows any ratio but alerts the user when the design may not physically fit.

#April 29, 2024 — Warning System Refinement
Fixed
Reduced false‑positive warnings by adding realistic tolerances.

Added ±0.05 inch tolerance for center‑distance matching.

Added 5% margin for wheel‑vs‑gear size comparison.

Warnings now trigger only when the mismatch is significant.
